		introduction: "undefined<br><br><span class=\"color_11\">Tuesday, Friday (4.30pm -7.30pm)</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">Wednesday (3-6pm)</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">Venue: Kah Kee Hall (High School)</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">Requirements: Strongly recommended to own a badminton racquet</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">How to Join: Trials</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">Participation in competition: Yes</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">Who to Contact:&nbsp;</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">Josiah Tan, Captain (Boys)&nbsp;</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">josiahtanej@hotmail.com (97926598)</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">Tan Si Jia, Captain (Girls)&nbsp;</span><br><br><span class=\"color_11\">sijia.tan@yahoo.com.sg (93867230) </span><br><br>",
		content: "Badminton is an indoor racquet sport played by either two opposing players (singles) or two opposing pairs (doubles), popular among people of all ages. <br><br>The team will consist of a team of players that will represent the school and participate in the annual National Schools Competition (End April – May). These players will be selected via trials. Competitive team members are expected to attend trainings that are thrice a week. The competitive team is coached by Mr Yeo, who is a dedicated, friendly and inspiring coach. To date, the best achievement is a 2nd placing in the annual competition. <br><br>Our CCA also aims to promote badminton among the student body, as well as provide a platform for students who share interest in badminton to meet and engage in friendly matches, and eventually forge friendships. Our team also aims to achieve tight-knit bonds whereby more experienced members will help out less experienced members with basic badminton skills for improvement in play. <br><br>Our CCA also aims to promote the game to the entire student body by organizing the annually held intra college badminton competition event ‘SMASH’. We are planning to execute this in mid-March. This event allows even non-members to come together and develop friendships through the sport. <br><br>The EXCO will spearhead either a CIP or SL project each year. <br><br>Upcoming Events:Mid-March: <br><br>SMASH – annual tournament opened to the school organised by the CCA<br><br>End April – May: National School Games – national tournament where school is represented by the competitive team <br><br>Do contact the following if you would like to know more about Badminton!<br><br>Teachers-in-charge: Mr Kwek (96667055)<br><br>C<br><br>",
