		introduction: "CCA Sessions: Wednesday (3.30pm-6pm), Friday (4.30pm -6.30pm)<br><br>Venue: SALT Centre Dance Studio<br><br>Requirements: Prior experience preferred<br><br>How to Join: Auditions<br><br>Participation in Competition: Yes <br><br>Who to Contact:<br><br>Kassie, President <br><br>97763860&nbsp;<br><br>Natalie, Vice President &nbsp;<br><br>81980718&nbsp;<br><br>",
		content: "Hwa Chong Chinese Dance (HCCD) consists of talented dancers with a strong passion for dance. Under the guidance of Ms Xiao Jing, an accomplished dancer and choreographer, HCCD has produced outstanding results.<br><br>HCCD clinched the highest accolades in the Singapore Youth Festival Central Judging (2009, 2011) as well as the Singapore Youth Festival Arts Presentation (2013, 2015). Apart from participating in the biannual Singapore Youth Festival, HCCD also performs for school events, such as the Chinese New Year celebrations, Mid-Autumn Festival celebrations and the Senior Promenade. <br><br>In addition, HCCD collaborates with Music and Dance (MAD) to stage dance concerts. HCCD is also privileged to have been invited to perform for prestigious events like the Chingay Parade in 2012 and 2015. Events that you can look forward to participate in include: Chinese New Year performance, Dance concert with MAD, Mid-Autumn Festival performance and Senior Promenade performance! <br><br>Join the HCCD family and be sure to enjoy learning Chinese Dance and participating in various exciting events! Contact Kassie (97763860) or Natalie (81980718) for more details!<br><br>",
