		content: "The Hwa Chong Chinese Orchestra(HCCO) was founded in 1974 and is currently under the baton of Dr. Wei Yanming, teacher-conductor, and Mr. Lum Yan Sing, advisor-cum-instructor. <br><br>Since 1977, the Orchestra has been taking part in the biennial Singapore Youth Festival (SYF) Chinese Orchestra Competition, having obtained a total of twelve medals to date. In 1985, the Chinese Orchestra was the only one to receive the \"outstanding\" award, and in 2003, it obtained the title of \"Best Junior College Chinese Orchestra\". <br><br>More recently, in 2005, 2007, 2009 and 2011, HCCO consecutively clinched the Gold with Honours award, becoming the only Junior College Chinese Orchestra to accomplish this feat since the award's inception in 2005. In 2015, the Chinese Orchestra continued to excel in the competition and achieved the Certificate of Distinction. <br><br>HCCO actively participates in both school and external events in order to constantly seek the betterment of their musicians’ calibre and promote their understanding and love for Chinese music. Apart from performing for the annual Open House, Chinese New Year Celebrations and the Mid Autumn Festival, the Orchestra prides itself in its biennial concert, themed “Heavenly Echoes” (“天籁回音”), which started in 1982. Over the years, HCCO has performed in the Victoria Concert Hall and the Singapore Conference Hall. In 2004, the orchestra was also invited to perform in the \"Mega Concert\" during Singapore's National Day.<br><br>In 1978, the Orchestra began organising annual inter-college Chinese Orchestra interaction programmes, which involves partner CCAs coming together for a day of exchange and fun activities, thereby forging friendships among students of different schools.<br><br>HCCO also strongly believes in giving back to society and constantly strives to uphold the value of compassion. It continues to work with Toa Payoh Care Corner and Renci Hospital, serving the elderly. Recently in 2015, the Orchestra performed for Ground-up Initiative’s Mega Balik Kampung event, and also organised a day of interaction with Pertapis Children’s Home. <br><br>To further nurture our students to become well-rounded individuals equipped with the awareness and sensitivities of foreign cultures, HCCO also brings its students on overseas immersion programmes, having been to Japan in 2010 and Taiwan in 2012 &amp; 2014.<br><br>Through these events, hard work and determination, the Hwa Chong Institution College Chinese Orchestra has been and will continue to uphold its tradition of excellence for many years to come.<br><br>",
