		introduction: "CCA Sessions: Wednesday (3pm-6pm), Friday (5pm-8pm)<br><br>Venue: Main Band Room at SALT Centre<br><br>undefined<br><br>undefined<br><br>undefined<br><br>undefined<br><br>undefined<br><br>undefined<br><br>undefined<br><br>undefined<br><br>",
		content: "The Hwa Chong Symphonic Band (also known as HCBand) began humbly as a small military band in 1974 and has since then flourished into the full symphonic band they are today. Under the baton of resident conductor Mr. Darence Leng, the band has gone on to clinch a Gold award at the Singapore Youth Festival (SYF) Central Judging for Junior College Bands in 2009, a Silver award in 2011 and the Certificate of Distinction in 2013 and 2015. Besides its achievements in SYF, HCBand has also achieved a gold award in the 2014 National Band Competition. <br><br>In recognition of their high musical standards, HCBand has been invited to perform in many biannual SYF Band Presentations since 1980. The band was also invited to the Shell-MOE Band Fiesta in 2003 to show off the more exuberant side of their playing. <br><br>HCBand holds at least one annual concert, testament to its members’ passion for music and their eagerness to share it. The band actively hosts and participates in exchanges with likeminded overseas peers to broaden their perspectives. <br><br>With the determination and effort put in by all the band members as well as the school’s continual support, HCBand will keep on striving for excellence as a band, and let their love for music live on. <br><br>",
